1
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:20,680
JENNY: (ECHOING)
Strax? Strax? Strax? Strax?

2
00:00:20,760 --> 00:00:23,600
-(ALARM BLARING)
-PA: Warning. Evacuate immediately.

3
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:29,840
Leave me. Go on.
You must leave me here to die.

4
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:31,800
You're not dying, Strax.

5
00:00:31,880 --> 00:00:34,400
It's fine. Don't worry.

6
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:38,280
It's a glorious thing
for a Sontaran to die in battle.

7
00:00:38,360 --> 00:00:41,400
The battle was two days ago.
You've made a full recovery!

8
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,880
-No, I haven't.
-We've healed your wounds!

9
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:45,240
You're completely fine.

10
00:00:45,320 --> 00:00:49,080
Nonsense! That was definitely
a fatal shot. I didn't stand a chance!

11
00:00:50,080 --> 00:00:51,440
I think you just fainted.

12
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:53,000
Silence, boy!

13
00:00:53,080 --> 00:00:54,920
The station is being evacuated.

14
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,280
We're all being returned
to our proper times and places.

15
00:00:58,360 --> 00:01:00,680
We wondered if you would
like to come with us.

16
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:03,960
We're from London. 1888.

17
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:06,720
What of it?
Is there something there for me?

18
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:07,800
A welcome?

19
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:10,640
-Why?
-We fought together, didn't we,

20
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:12,240
side by side as comrades?

21
00:01:12,320 --> 00:01:15,680
And we couldn't help noticing,
you do seem to be...

22
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:16,760
alone.

23
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:19,080
I am accustomed to solitude.

24
00:01:19,160 --> 00:01:20,360
As are we.

25
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:23,400
Jenny here has been ostracised
by her family because of...

26
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:28,640
Well, let's just say
preferences in companionship.

27
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:32,400
I am the last of my kind,
as you are the only one of yours.

28
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:35,960
A Sontaran who fought
bravely in the best of causes.

29
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:42,320
I thank you for your offer,
but cannot accept,

30
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,600
as you are putrescent alien filth.

31
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:49,400
Indeed. We thought
that would be a difficulty.

32
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:54,680
(SIGHING) Come along, Jenny.
Time to go home.

33
00:01:56,320 --> 00:02:00,920
Although...
This planet of which you speak, London,

34
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:02,320
what do you do there?

35
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:03,680
Solve crimes.

36
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:05,120
Protect the Empire.

37
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,600
There's quite a lot of running.

38
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:08,440
Some spectacular dresses.

39
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:10,520
And an awful lot of fun.

40
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:17,720
I suppose I could make a preliminary
reconnaissance of this London place.

41
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,160
It may need to be assessed
for military potential.

42
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,760
That's the spirit!

43
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,200
Thank you for this opportunity.

44
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:26,960
I look forward to obliterating you both
in the name of the Sontaran empire.

45
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:33,280
I'm not an expert on alien species,
but you're both women ones, aren't you?

46
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:35,480
It has been noted.

47
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:37,880
Don't you need a man one?

48
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:39,680
BOTH: No.

49
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:41,400
Am I the man one?

50
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:42,800
BOTH: No!

51
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,400
So! Dresses, then!

